<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.oilcrash.com/articles/arnett05.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.oilcrash.com/articles/arnett05.htm" rel="nofollow">Peak Oil, Total Collapse, and the Road to the Olduvai</a> - Perry Arnett, April 18 2007, www.oilcrash.com</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.fao.org/english/newsroom/news/2002/7828-en.html" class="external text" title="http://www.fao.org/english/newsroom/news/2002/7828-en.html" rel="nofollow">World agriculture 2030: Global food production will exceed population growth</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.eia.doe.gov/pub/international/iealf/tablee1c.xls" class="external text" title="http://www.eia.doe.gov/pub/international/iealf/tablee1c.xls" rel="nofollow">World Per Capita Total Primary Energy Consumption, 1980-2006</a> - Energy Information Administration, 2006 (Excel Sheet)</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.physics.uci.edu/~silverma/units.html" class="external text" title="http://www.physics.uci.edu/~silverma/units.html" rel="nofollow">Energy Units and Conversions</a> - Dennis Silverman, UC Irvine</li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.theoildrum.com/story/2006/3/6/135437/7111" class="external text" title="http://www.theoildrum.com/story/2006/3/6/135437/7111" rel="nofollow">Revisiting the Olduvai Theory</a> - The Oil Drum, March 6, 2006</li>
</ol>
